ok, fixed the issue with saving changes to a current workshop and sending them while in session, it will now issue a refresh on that current template if you do so. So you can now in effect make those changes and send them up stream and its all fine they will reflect

Its tracking the current loaded workshop, if the same workshop is sent over it just issues a refresh of the current template loaded. if its not the same workshop it will reset back to the first mode of that workshop being morning
so if you change workshop name it starts over if you save with same name it will pick up during the right preset?

yup, but you cant change the workshop name without making a massive change anyways, since its locked to the brand name you have selected, which is locking in cubby assignment and users in your workshop
and workshop name is never shown or used anywhere in the system other than the admin UI and this check

ok.  does saving at the workshop level reset the preset to the begining IE re-save lunch at 12:15, does preset continue to only play til 12:30 or does the system think its 12pm again at time of re-save?
workshops have nothing to do with time flow, the scheduler runs its own tick off the real clock. saving the workshop does nothing but refresh the current view putting changes made into effect
